# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# frame_sources.conf.example
#
# TEMPLATE FILE - Copy this to frame_sources.conf and customize for your setup
#
# Defines all available photo sources for PicFrame.
# Format for each source:
#
#     id|label|absolute_path|enabled|rclone_remote
#
# where:
#   id            = unique short identifier (used by CLI & scripts)
#   label         = human-friendly name (shown in menus/web UI)
#   absolute_path = directory containing the photos on the Pi
#   enabled       = 1 = selectable, 0 = shown but disabled
#   rclone_remote = (optional) rclone remote:path for this source
#
# NOTE:
#   - You can add as many sources as you want â€” no script changes needed.
#   - Disabled sources still show up in the menu but cannot be selected.
#   - If rclone_remote is omitted, the global RCLONE_REMOTE from config is used.
#   - Add your sources via the dashboard or manually edit this file
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

# Example sources (uncomment and customize):
# gdt|Google Drive Photos|/home/pi/Pictures/gdt_frame|1|gdrive:photos
# kfr|Koofr Photos|/home/pi/Pictures/kfr_frame|1|koofr:MyPhotos

# Additional example sources:
# usb|USB Flash Drive|/mnt/usb/frame|0|
# nas|NAS Family Photos|/mnt/nas/photos|0|
# drop|Dropbox Export|/mnt/dropbox/frame|0|dropbox:frame
